The paper deals with the problem of approximating the quality of a disperser and bipartite expander, which are both related to graph theory and combinatorics. The paper also mentions the Lasserre hierarchy, which is a common tool in computational complexity and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT), computational geometry (cs.CG), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM), which are all relevant to the topic.
